http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Pratishthana-to-urge-government-to-open-a-varsity-for-Yakshagana/article14016954.ece

The eleventh Akhil Bharat Yakshagana-Bayalata-Sahitya Sammelan, a convention on Yakshagana and Bayalata art forms, held here recently under the aegis of the Karnataka Samskrutika Kala Pratishthana, has passed a resolution to urge the State government to establish a separate university focussing on Yakshagana.Dattamurthy Bhat, vice-president of the pratishthana, said in a press release issued here on Saturday that the proposed university should undertake study and research on Yakshagana and provide training to youths in the art.CurriculumThe convention passed another resolution to demand inclusion of the poems and prasangas of Yakshagana in school syllabus to instil interest among students on this art form, he said in the release.